  "summary": "Fragile bounds check when sampling from image",
  "details": "A read of pixels was coded as modifying coordinates to lie within the image\nbounds. It would calculate a coordinate by adding a constant to an input and\ntaking the minimum of the resulting coordinate and 'dimension - 1'. This would\nnot protect against malicious inputs that could overflow the addition. .\nSubsequently to the tricked bounds check the image could then be sampled at\nmultiple, differently calculated coordinates exceeding the bounds.",
